Then, slowly, almost imperceptibly, something shifted again.
I could feel it coming (the way you feel weather changing in your bones).

Chapter 7

It started with a canceled dinner.
“I’m buried under deadlines,” she texted. “Can we postpone?”
Of course I understood.
But something twisted hard in my chest all the same.
The next day her replies came hours late.
I sent her a long voice note about a thought we’d shared two nights earlier (something small that had felt huge in the dark). She answered with three words: “Yes, exactly that.”
