For most people that wouldn’t be a crisis.
For me (someone who had lived on immediacy, on being wanted the second I reached out), it felt like someone had switched off the sun.
I caught myself checking my phone every thirty seconds.
Re-reading old messages like an addict.
Trying to decode pauses that probably meant nothing.
But to me those pauses screamed one thing:
She’s slipping away.
And I still don’t know how to exist if I’m not being watched.
