Chapter 8

The next morning her message came.
No greeting.
No warmth.
Just a single line, gentle and merciless:
“I saw your video.
You don’t have to choose me.
But you have to choose which version of yourself you want to keep feeding.”
I typed replies and deleted them for an hour.
What could I possibly say?
That I panicked?
That silence still feels like dying?
That I’m terrified I only exist when someone’s watching?
An hour later she wrote again:
“I’m here.
But not if you keep running back to who you were before.”
Then came days of near-silence (not cruel, just distance). A distance that closed the walls of my old life around me like a coffin.
The compliments on the relapse video turned to ash in my mouth. My phone never stopped buzzing, but none of it reached me. It was noise.
