I didn’t promise I’d never relapse.
I promised I’d never again use what we have to feed the void.
“I can’t swear the hunger will disappear,” I said, voice rough. “But I swear I’ll never let it touch us again.”
She listened, fingers wrapped around her cup.
“I can’t promise I won’t overthink,” she said softly. “But I can promise to stay, even when I’m scared.”
“And I shouldn’t have said that thing about you wanting an audience.
That was me speaking from fear, not truth.”
Silence settled between us (warm, for the first time in weeks).
